While there are several advantages to using a ready-made WordPress theme, there are also some disadvantages to consider:

In summary, the choice between using a custom-made WordPress theme or a ready-made WordPress theme depends on your specific needs and preferences. Custom-made WordPress themes offer greater flexibility and customization options, while ready-made WordPress themes offer convenience and cost-effectiveness. Ultimately, the best decision will depend on your specific requirements and budget.

```
git remote add origin https://github.com/<username>/<reponame>.git

Replace `<username>` with your GitHub username and `<reponame>` with the name of your forked repository.

Push the changes to your forked repository:

```
Note: `main` refers to the default branch in your forked repository. If your forked repository uses a different default branch, replace `main` with that branch name. 

After you push your changes, you can create a pull request on your forked repository's page on GitHub. In the pull request, you can describe the changes you made and request that they be merged into the original repository.

�ānān, (born c. 930—died c. 1020), Persian poet whose works are among the most popular in the Persian language.
The son of a military commander, he grew up in Kāshān, where he received a traditional Islamic education. He entered the service of the Seljuq sultan Mahmūd of Ghazna but soon left to lead a hermit’s life. After a brief period in retirement, he resumed his travels, eventually finding a patron in the Ghaznavid ruler Mas‘ūd I.
The ghazal (love lyric) is the dominant form of his poetry, which is marked by a strong personal note and by an intense feeling for nature. His poems, which are often mystical in tone, frequently express his love for a young man, ‘Ammīrī.
The Diwān, his complete works, is divided into five sections: the first, "The Mathnawī," consists of a lengthy didactic poem in rhymed prose; the remaining four sections, known as the "rubā‘iyyāt" ("quatrains"), contain a collection of about 4,500 lyrical poems.
Although Hafiz’s poetry was highly esteemed by Persian literary figures of the 16th through 19th centuries, it was largely ignored by Western scholars until the late 18th century. Since then his works have been frequently translated into English and other Western languages. Hafiz has also had a considerable influence on the Persian language itself.
